<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90f43c4e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8005"><num value="8005">§ 8005.</num><heading> Inoperability of determination and waivers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A determination and any waiver under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s8003">section 8003 of this title</ref> shall cease to be effective if the President determines that India has detonated a nuclear explosive device after <date date="2006-12-18">December 18, 2006</date>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id90f43c4f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/401/tI/s106">Pub. L. 109–401, title I, § 106</ref>, <date date="2006-12-18">Dec. 18, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/2738">120 Stat. 2738</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
